cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it presents an efficient framework for generating a motion plan for a robot with high degrees of freedom. The use of Gaussian process latent variable model (GP-LVM) and an approximate inference algorithm also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of a supplemental video suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of duality between control and estimation suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
